Direct Known Subclasses:
DefaultBiIndexImpl
public class DefaultIndexImpl<KeyType,ValueType>
extends Object
implements org.hypergraphdb.HGSortIndex<KeyType,ValueType>

A default index implementation. This implementation works by maintaining a separate DB, using a B-tree, byte [] lexicographical ordering on its keys. The keys are therefore assumed to by byte [] instances.

Author:
Borislav Iordanov

findLast

public ValueType findLast(KeyType key)

Find the last entry, assuming ordered duplicates, corresponding to the given key.

Parameters:
key - The key whose last entry is sought.
Returns:
The last (i.e. greatest, i.e. maximum) data value for that key or null if the set of entries for the key is empty.
